# wgpu-py Skill

## Overview

`wgpu-py` is a Python binding for the [WebGPU](https://gpuweb.github.io/gpuweb/)
API, implemented via [`wgpu-native`](https://github.com/gfx-rs/wgpu-native)
(a Rust library). Use it to run GPU computations and GPU rendering from Python
without needing OpenGL, Vulkan, Metal, or DX12 directly.

- Install: `pip install wgpu`
- Rendering to a window requires `rendercanvas`: `pip install rendercanvas`
- Official docs: <https://wgpu-py.readthedocs.io/en/stable/>

---

## Core Concepts

| Concept | wgpu class | Purpose |
|---------|-----------|---------|
| API entry-point | `wgpu.gpu` (`GPU`) | `request_adapter_sync()` |
| Adapter | `GPUAdapter` | Represents a physical/virtual GPU |
| Device | `GPUDevice` | Central object; creates all other GPU objects |
| Buffer | `GPUBuffer` | Raw memory on the GPU |
| Texture | `GPUTexture` | Image data (1-D / 2-D / 3-D) |
| Texture view | `GPUTextureView` | Typed view into a texture |
| Sampler | `GPUSampler` | Filtering / address-mode descriptor |
| Shader module | `GPUShaderModule` | Compiled WGSL or SPIR-V program |
| Bind-group layout | `GPUBindGroupLayout` | Describes resource slot types |
| Bind group | `GPUBindGroup` | Actual resource bindings used by a pipeline |
| Pipeline layout | `GPUPipelineLayout` | Collection of bind-group layouts |
| Compute pipeline | `GPUComputePipeline` | GPU compute dispatch |
| Render pipeline | `GPURenderPipeline` | Vertex + fragment draw call |
| Command encoder | `GPUCommandEncoder` | Records a series of GPU commands |
| Render pass encoder | `GPURenderPassEncoder` | Records render commands |
| Compute pass encoder | `GPUComputePassEncoder` | Records compute commands |
| Queue | `GPUQueue` | Submits recorded command buffers |
| Canvas context | `GPUCanvasContext` | Bridge to a window surface |

