## WGSL Shader Guidelines

- WGSL is the shading language for WebGPU / wgpu-py.
- Use `@group(G) @binding(B)` annotations to match Python bind-group setup.
- Use `var<storage, read>` for input-only buffers and
  `var<storage, read_write>` for output buffers in compute shaders.
- Use `@workgroup_size(64)` as a sensible default for 1-D compute dispatches.
- Reference: <https://www.w3.org/TR/WGSL/>

```wgsl
// Example: element-wise multiply of two arrays
@group(0) @binding(0) var<storage, read>       a : array<f32>;
@group(0) @binding(1) var<storage, read>       b : array<f32>;
@group(0) @binding(2) var<storage, read_write> c : array<f32>;

@compute @workgroup_size(64)
fn main(@builtin(global_invocation_id) gid : vec3<u32>) {
    let i = gid.x;
    if (i < arrayLength(&a)) {
        c[i] = a[i] * b[i];
    }
}
```

