## Debugging Tips

- Set `WGPU_BACKEND_TYPE` env var to `"Vulkan"`, `"Metal"`, `"D3D12"`, or
  `"OpenGL"` to force a specific backend.
- Enable verbose logging:
  ```python
  import logging
  logging.getLogger("wgpu").setLevel(logging.DEBUG)
  ```
- Give GPU objects a `label` argument — labels appear in validation errors
  and in RenderDoc.
- Run the application via [RenderDoc](https://renderdoc.org/) to capture a
  frame and inspect all draw calls and resource states.
- Print adapter / device diagnostics:
  ```python
  wgpu.diagnostics.print_report()
  ```

