## Key API Quick Reference

| Operation | Python call |
|-----------|------------|
| Get default device | `wgpu.utils.get_default_device()` |
| Request adapter | `wgpu.gpu.request_adapter_sync(power_preference=...)` |
| Request device | `adapter.request_device_sync()` |
| Create buffer | `device.create_buffer(size=..., usage=...)` |
| Create buffer with data | `device.create_buffer_with_data(data=..., usage=...)` |
| Write buffer | `device.queue.write_buffer(buffer, offset, data)` |
| Read buffer | `device.queue.read_buffer(buffer)` |
| Create texture | `device.create_texture(size=..., format=..., usage=...)` |
| Write texture | `device.queue.write_texture(dest, data, layout, size)` |
| Read texture | `device.queue.read_texture(source, layout, size)` |
| Create shader | `device.create_shader_module(code=wgsl_string)` |
| Create compute pipeline | `device.create_compute_pipeline(layout=..., compute=...)` |
| Create render pipeline | `device.create_render_pipeline(layout=..., vertex=..., ...)` |
| Command encoder | `device.create_command_encoder()` |
| Submit commands | `device.queue.submit([encoder.finish()])` |
| Print diagnostics | `wgpu.diagnostics.print_report()` |
````


